message.text:
Mabuhay!

MICE Class Section 5 would like to invite your respective classes in our upcoming event entitled "Navigating the Research Lifecycle: From Idea to Impactful Publication."  On Sept 22, 2025 from 9am-12nn at the main auditorium. 

See you!

𝐄𝐯𝐞𝐫𝐲 𝐠𝐫𝐞𝐚𝐭 𝐝𝐢𝐬𝐜𝐨𝐯𝐞𝐫𝐲 𝐛𝐞𝐠𝐢𝐧𝐬 𝐰𝐢𝐭𝐡 𝐚 𝐬𝐢𝐧𝐠𝐥𝐞 𝐢𝐝𝐞𝐚.
�Be part of “𝐍𝐚𝐯𝐢𝐠𝐚𝐭𝐢𝐧𝐠 𝐭𝐡𝐞 𝐑𝐞𝐬𝐞𝐚𝐫𝐜𝐡 𝐋𝐢𝐟𝐞𝐜𝐲𝐜𝐥𝐞: 𝐅𝐫𝐨𝐦 𝐈𝐝𝐞𝐚 𝐭𝐨 𝐈𝐦𝐩𝐚𝐜𝐭𝐟𝐮𝐥 𝐏𝐮𝐛𝐥𝐢𝐜𝐚𝐭𝐢𝐨𝐧,” where you’ll learn how to nurture your ideas into impactful work that inspires change.

🗓 𝗦𝗲𝗽𝘁𝗲𝗺𝗯𝗲𝗿 𝟮𝟮, 𝟮𝟬𝟮𝟱 (𝗠𝗼𝗻𝗱𝗮𝘆)�⏰ 𝟵:𝟬𝟬 𝗔𝗠 – 𝟭𝟮:𝟬𝟬 𝗡𝗡�📍 𝗙𝗘𝗨 𝗠𝗮𝗶𝗻 𝗔𝘂𝗱𝗶𝘁𝗼𝗿𝗶𝘂𝗺

𝐒𝐚𝐯𝐞 𝐭𝐡𝐞 𝐝𝐚𝐭𝐞! 𝐁𝐞𝐜𝐚𝐮𝐬𝐞 𝐞𝐯𝐞𝐫𝐲 𝐢𝐦𝐩𝐚𝐜𝐭𝐟𝐮𝐥 𝐫𝐞𝐬𝐞𝐚𝐫𝐜𝐡 𝐬𝐭𝐚𝐫𝐭𝐬 𝐰𝐢𝐭𝐡 𝐬𝐡𝐨𝐰𝐢𝐧𝐠 𝐮𝐩 𝐟𝐨𝐫 𝐢𝐝𝐞𝐚𝐬. This seminar is 𝐨𝐩𝐞𝐧 𝐭𝐨 𝐚𝐥𝐥 who wish to expand their knowledge and passion for research.

𝐑𝐞𝐚𝐝𝐲 𝐭𝐨 𝐭𝐮𝐫𝐧 𝐢𝐝𝐞𝐚𝐬 𝐢𝐧𝐭𝐨 𝐢𝐦𝐩𝐚𝐜𝐭? 𝐑𝐞𝐠𝐢𝐬𝐭𝐞𝐫 𝐧𝐨𝐰:

https://forms.cloud.microsoft/r/3uqexSjxay
https://forms.cloud.microsoft/r/3uqexSjxay
https://forms.cloud.microsoft/r/3uqexSjxay

E-certificates will be given to all participants.

message.text:
Mabuhay!

MICE Class Section 5 would like to invite your respective classes in our upcoming event entitled "Navigating the Research Lifecycle: From Idea to Impactful Publication."  On Sept 22, 2025 from 9am-12nn at the main auditorium. 

See you!

𝐄𝐯𝐞𝐫𝐲 𝐠𝐫𝐞𝐚𝐭 𝐝𝐢𝐬𝐜𝐨𝐯𝐞𝐫𝐲 𝐛𝐞𝐠𝐢𝐧𝐬 𝐰𝐢𝐭𝐡 𝐚 𝐬𝐢𝐧𝐠𝐥𝐞 𝐢𝐝𝐞𝐚.
�Be part of “𝐍𝐚𝐯𝐢𝐠𝐚𝐭𝐢𝐧𝐠 𝐭𝐡𝐞 𝐑𝐞𝐬𝐞𝐚𝐫𝐜𝐡 𝐋𝐢𝐟𝐞𝐜𝐲𝐜𝐥𝐞: 𝐅𝐫𝐨𝐦 𝐈𝐝𝐞𝐚 𝐭𝐨 𝐈𝐦𝐩𝐚𝐜𝐭𝐟𝐮𝐥 𝐏𝐮𝐛𝐥𝐢𝐜𝐚𝐭𝐢𝐨𝐧,” where you’ll learn how to nurture your ideas into impactful work that inspires change.

🗓 𝗦𝗲𝗽𝘁𝗲𝗺𝗯𝗲𝗿 𝟮𝟮, 𝟮𝟬𝟮𝟱 (𝗠𝗼𝗻𝗱𝗮𝘆)�⏰ 𝟵:𝟬𝟬 𝗔𝗠 – 𝟭𝟮:𝟬𝟬 𝗡𝗡�📍 𝗙𝗘𝗨 𝗠𝗮𝗶𝗻 𝗔𝘂𝗱𝗶𝘁𝗼𝗿𝗶𝘂𝗺

𝐒𝐚𝐯𝐞 𝐭𝐡𝐞 𝐝𝐚𝐭𝐞! 𝐁𝐞𝐜𝐚𝐮𝐬𝐞 𝐞𝐯𝐞𝐫𝐲 𝐢𝐦𝐩𝐚𝐜𝐭𝐟𝐮𝐥 𝐫𝐞𝐬𝐞𝐚𝐫𝐜𝐡 𝐬𝐭𝐚𝐫𝐭𝐬 𝐰𝐢𝐭𝐡 𝐬𝐡𝐨𝐰𝐢𝐧𝐠 𝐮𝐩 𝐟𝐨𝐫 𝐢𝐝𝐞𝐚𝐬. This seminar is 𝐨𝐩𝐞𝐧 𝐭𝐨 𝐚𝐥𝐥 who wish to expand their knowledge and passion for research.

𝐑𝐞𝐚𝐝𝐲 𝐭𝐨 𝐭𝐮𝐫𝐧 𝐢𝐝𝐞𝐚𝐬 𝐢𝐧𝐭𝐨 𝐢𝐦𝐩𝐚𝐜𝐭? 𝐑𝐞𝐠𝐢𝐬𝐭𝐞𝐫 𝐧𝐨𝐰:

https://forms.cloud.microsoft/r/3uqexSjxay
https://forms.cloud.microsoft/r/3uqexSjxay
https://forms.cloud.microsoft/r/3uqexSjxay

E-certificates will be given to all participants.

Mabuhay!

MICE Class Section 5 would like to invite your respective classes in our upcoming event entitled "Navigating the Research Lifecycle: From Idea to Impactful Publication."  On Sept 22, 2025 from 9am-12nn at the main auditorium. 

See you!

𝐄𝐯𝐞𝐫𝐲 𝐠𝐫𝐞𝐚𝐭 𝐝𝐢𝐬𝐜𝐨𝐯𝐞𝐫𝐲 𝐛𝐞𝐠𝐢𝐧𝐬 𝐰𝐢𝐭𝐡 𝐚 𝐬𝐢𝐧𝐠𝐥𝐞 𝐢𝐝𝐞𝐚.
�Be part of “𝐍𝐚𝐯𝐢𝐠𝐚𝐭𝐢𝐧𝐠 𝐭𝐡𝐞 𝐑𝐞𝐬𝐞𝐚𝐫𝐜𝐡 𝐋𝐢𝐟𝐞𝐜𝐲𝐜𝐥𝐞: 𝐅𝐫𝐨𝐦 𝐈𝐝𝐞𝐚 𝐭𝐨 𝐈𝐦𝐩𝐚𝐜𝐭𝐟𝐮𝐥 𝐏𝐮𝐛𝐥𝐢𝐜𝐚𝐭𝐢𝐨𝐧,” where you’ll learn how to nurture your ideas into impactful work that inspires change.

🗓 𝗦𝗲𝗽𝘁𝗲𝗺𝗯𝗲𝗿 𝟮𝟮, 𝟮𝟬𝟮𝟱 (𝗠𝗼𝗻𝗱𝗮𝘆)�⏰ 𝟵:𝟬𝟬 𝗔𝗠 – 𝟭𝟮:𝟬𝟬 𝗡𝗡�📍 𝗙𝗘𝗨 𝗠𝗮𝗶𝗻 𝗔𝘂𝗱𝗶𝘁𝗼𝗿𝗶𝘂𝗺

𝐒𝐚𝐯𝐞 𝐭𝐡𝐞 𝐝𝐚𝐭𝐞! 𝐁𝐞𝐜𝐚𝐮𝐬𝐞 𝐞𝐯𝐞𝐫𝐲 𝐢𝐦𝐩𝐚𝐜𝐭𝐟𝐮𝐥 𝐫𝐞𝐬𝐞𝐚𝐫𝐜𝐡 𝐬𝐭𝐚𝐫𝐭𝐬 𝐰𝐢𝐭𝐡 𝐬𝐡𝐨𝐰𝐢𝐧𝐠 𝐮𝐩 𝐟𝐨𝐫 𝐢𝐝𝐞𝐚𝐬. This seminar is 𝐨𝐩𝐞𝐧 𝐭𝐨 𝐚𝐥𝐥 who wish to expand their knowledge and passion for research.

𝐑𝐞𝐚𝐝𝐲 𝐭𝐨 𝐭𝐮𝐫𝐧 𝐢𝐝𝐞𝐚𝐬 𝐢𝐧𝐭𝐨 𝐢𝐦𝐩𝐚𝐜𝐭? 𝐑𝐞𝐠𝐢𝐬𝐭𝐞𝐫 𝐧𝐨𝐰:

https://forms.cloud.microsoft/r/3uqexSjxay
https://forms.cloud.microsoft/r/3uqexSjxay
https://forms.cloud.microsoft/r/3uqexSjxay

E-certificates will be given to all participants.

See you!

🗓 𝗦𝗲𝗽𝘁𝗲𝗺𝗯𝗲𝗿 𝟮𝟮, 𝟮𝟬𝟮𝟱 (𝗠𝗼𝗻𝗱𝗮𝘆)�⏰ 𝟵:𝟬𝟬 𝗔𝗠 – 𝟭𝟮:𝟬𝟬 𝗡𝗡�📍 𝗙𝗘𝗨 𝗠𝗮𝗶𝗻 𝗔𝘂𝗱𝗶𝘁𝗼𝗿𝗶𝘂𝗺

See you!

𝐒𝐚𝐯𝐞 𝐭𝐡𝐞 𝐝𝐚𝐭𝐞! 𝐁𝐞𝐜𝐚𝐮𝐬𝐞 𝐞𝐯𝐞𝐫𝐲 𝐢𝐦𝐩𝐚𝐜𝐭𝐟𝐮𝐥 𝐫𝐞𝐬𝐞𝐚𝐫𝐜𝐡 𝐬𝐭𝐚𝐫𝐭𝐬 𝐰𝐢𝐭𝐡 𝐬𝐡𝐨𝐰𝐢𝐧𝐠 𝐮𝐩 𝐟𝐨𝐫 𝐢𝐝𝐞𝐚𝐬. This seminar is 𝐨𝐩𝐞𝐧 𝐭𝐨 𝐚𝐥𝐥 who wish to expand their knowledge and passion for research.

Mabuhay!

See you!

𝐄𝐯𝐞𝐫𝐲 𝐠𝐫𝐞𝐚𝐭 𝐝𝐢𝐬𝐜𝐨𝐯𝐞𝐫𝐲 𝐛𝐞𝐠𝐢𝐧𝐬 𝐰𝐢𝐭𝐡 𝐚 𝐬𝐢𝐧𝐠𝐥𝐞 𝐢𝐝𝐞𝐚.

𝐒𝐚𝐯𝐞 𝐭𝐡𝐞 𝐝𝐚𝐭𝐞! 𝐁𝐞𝐜𝐚𝐮𝐬𝐞 𝐞𝐯𝐞𝐫𝐲 𝐢𝐦𝐩𝐚𝐜𝐭𝐟𝐮𝐥 𝐫𝐞𝐬𝐞𝐚𝐫𝐜𝐡 𝐬𝐭𝐚𝐫𝐭𝐬 𝐰𝐢𝐭𝐡 𝐬𝐡𝐨𝐰𝐢𝐧𝐠 𝐮𝐩 𝐟𝐨𝐫 𝐢𝐝𝐞𝐚𝐬. This seminar is 𝐨𝐩𝐞𝐧 𝐭𝐨 𝐚𝐥𝐥 who wish to expand their knowledge and passion for research.

message.text:
Mabuhay!

MICE Class Section 5 would like to invite your respective classes in our upcoming event entitled "Navigating the Research Lifecycle: From Idea to Impactful Publication."  On Sept 22, 2025 from 9am-12nn at the main auditorium. 

See you!

𝐄𝐯𝐞𝐫𝐲 𝐠𝐫𝐞𝐚𝐭 𝐝𝐢𝐬𝐜𝐨𝐯𝐞𝐫𝐲 𝐛𝐞𝐠𝐢𝐧𝐬 𝐰𝐢𝐭𝐡 𝐚 𝐬𝐢𝐧𝐠𝐥𝐞 𝐢𝐝𝐞𝐚.
�Be part of “𝐍𝐚𝐯𝐢𝐠𝐚𝐭𝐢𝐧𝐠 𝐭𝐡𝐞 𝐑𝐞𝐬𝐞𝐚𝐫𝐜𝐡 𝐋𝐢𝐟𝐞𝐜𝐲𝐜𝐥𝐞: 𝐅𝐫𝐨𝐦 𝐈𝐝𝐞𝐚 𝐭𝐨 𝐈𝐦𝐩𝐚𝐜𝐭𝐟𝐮𝐥 𝐏𝐮𝐛𝐥𝐢𝐜𝐚𝐭𝐢𝐨𝐧,” where you’ll learn how to nurture your ideas into impactful work that inspires change.

🗓 𝗦𝗲𝗽𝘁𝗲𝗺𝗯𝗲𝗿 𝟮𝟮, 𝟮𝟬𝟮𝟱 (𝗠𝗼𝗻𝗱𝗮𝘆)�⏰ 𝟵:𝟬𝟬 𝗔𝗠 – 𝟭𝟮:𝟬𝟬 𝗡𝗡�📍 𝗙𝗘𝗨 𝗠𝗮𝗶𝗻 𝗔𝘂𝗱𝗶𝘁𝗼𝗿𝗶𝘂𝗺

𝐒𝐚𝐯𝐞 𝐭𝐡𝐞 𝐝𝐚𝐭𝐞! 𝐁𝐞𝐜𝐚𝐮𝐬𝐞 𝐞𝐯𝐞𝐫𝐲 𝐢𝐦𝐩𝐚𝐜𝐭𝐟𝐮𝐥 𝐫𝐞𝐬𝐞𝐚𝐫𝐜𝐡 𝐬𝐭𝐚𝐫𝐭𝐬 𝐰𝐢𝐭𝐡 𝐬𝐡𝐨𝐰𝐢𝐧𝐠 𝐮𝐩 𝐟𝐨𝐫 𝐢𝐝𝐞𝐚𝐬. This seminar is 𝐨𝐩𝐞𝐧 𝐭𝐨 𝐚𝐥𝐥 who wish to expand their knowledge and passion for research.

𝐑𝐞𝐚𝐝𝐲 𝐭𝐨 𝐭𝐮𝐫𝐧 𝐢𝐝𝐞𝐚𝐬 𝐢𝐧𝐭𝐨 𝐢𝐦𝐩𝐚𝐜𝐭? 𝐑𝐞𝐠𝐢𝐬𝐭𝐞𝐫 𝐧𝐨𝐰:

https://forms.cloud.microsoft/r/3uqexSjxay
https://forms.cloud.microsoft/r/3uqexSjxay
https://forms.cloud.microsoft/r/3uqexSjxay

E-certificates will be given to all participants.

message.text:
Did you know tourism is making its strongest comeback in 2025?

𝐓𝐡𝐢𝐬 𝐖𝐨𝐫𝐥𝐝 𝐓𝐨𝐮𝐫𝐢𝐬𝐦 𝐃𝐚𝐲, 𝐜𝐞𝐥𝐞𝐛𝐫𝐚𝐭𝐞 𝐭𝐡𝐞 𝐭𝐡𝐞𝐦𝐞: “𝐓𝐨𝐮𝐫𝐢𝐬𝐦 𝐚𝐧𝐝 𝐒𝐮𝐬𝐭𝐚𝐢𝐧𝐚𝐛𝐥𝐞 𝐓𝐫𝐚𝐧𝐬𝐟𝐨𝐫𝐦𝐚𝐭𝐢𝐨𝐧” by embracing responsible travel that benefits local communities, preserves culture, and protects the environment. Voluntourism is a rising trend, especially among Millennials and Gen Z, where travel becomes a meaningful mission to give back through education, conservation, and community projects.

This year, the call for “Tourism and Sustainable Transformation” encourages everyone to rethink how tourism is developed and experienced. It’s about balancing economic growth with preserving natural ecosystems and cultural heritage, while empowering local communities through inclusive policies and innovative practices. 

Together, these efforts transform tourism into a sustainable force that benefits both travelers and the places they visit. 🌍

Caption by: Patrick Blas
Pubmat by: Miguelito Lalu

#PATAPHFEU
#WTD2025

media.accessibility_caption: May be an image of text that says "PATA သးထ PAITYERSHIFONTH PARTYERSH HIU ศ tamang bote WORLD Jourism JourismQay Qay "Tourism brings together" -Antonio Guterres"

May be a graphic of 1 person, map and text that says "PATA SE History PAKTYERSHII ONTTT tamang bate World Tourism Day is commemorated annually on 27 September to foster awareness among the international community of the importance of tourism and its social, cultural, political, and economic value. September 27 27 Designed or Coincidence? The annual celebration of World Tourism Day was strategically picked to symbolize unity in tourism. World Tourism Day was established on September 27, 1970 because it marks the end of the tourism season in the Northern Hemisphere and the start of the tourism season in the Southern Hemisphere (Reali, 2025)."

May be an image of map and text that says "PATA 自に品 PATEISHIFONN tamang bote World Tourism Day 2025 Theme : Tourism Sustainable Transformation Tourism is not just about travel, it's the drive towards sustainable change. With this year's theme, "Tourism and Sustainable Transformation", highlights how tourism celebrates its power as an agent of positive change. When done responsibly, tourişm benefits the locals, preserves cultural heritage, fosters economic growth, and promotes environmental conservation."

May be an image of tree and text that says "PATA သးသသး။ PARTYERSHIIOHTT PARTYERSHI tamang bote Volunteerism and Voluntourism Volunteerism comes in many forms but each action portrays single message the spirit of service, responsibility, and solidarity. The growing popularity of voluntourism reflects broader tourism trends (McGehee, 2014), especially among Millennials and Gen who value global citizenship and meaningful engagement (Bank,2021). Through voluntourism, they contribute education, conservation, and community projects turning travel into something more meaningful and sustainable. This makes every travel mission and a destination that benefits both the visitor and the host community."

message.text:
Did you know tourism is making its strongest comeback in 2025?

𝐓𝐡𝐢𝐬 𝐖𝐨𝐫𝐥𝐝 𝐓𝐨𝐮𝐫𝐢𝐬𝐦 𝐃𝐚𝐲, 𝐜𝐞𝐥𝐞𝐛𝐫𝐚𝐭𝐞 𝐭𝐡𝐞 𝐭𝐡𝐞𝐦𝐞: “𝐓𝐨𝐮𝐫𝐢𝐬𝐦 𝐚𝐧𝐝 𝐒𝐮𝐬𝐭𝐚𝐢𝐧𝐚𝐛𝐥𝐞 𝐓𝐫𝐚𝐧𝐬𝐟𝐨𝐫𝐦𝐚𝐭𝐢𝐨𝐧” by embracing responsible travel that benefits local communities, preserves culture, and protects the environment. Voluntourism is a rising trend, especially among Millennials and Gen Z, where travel becomes a meaningful mission to give back through education, conservation, and community projects.

This year, the call for “Tourism and Sustainable Transformation” encourages everyone to rethink how tourism is developed and experienced. It’s about balancing economic growth with preserving natural ecosystems and cultural heritage, while empowering local communities through inclusive policies and innovative practices. 

Together, these efforts transform tourism into a sustainable force that benefits both travelers and the places they visit. 🌍

Caption by: Patrick Blas
Pubmat by: Miguelito Lalu

#PATAPHFEU
#WTD2025

message.text:
Did you know tourism is making its strongest comeback in 2025?

𝐓𝐡𝐢𝐬 𝐖𝐨𝐫𝐥𝐝 𝐓𝐨𝐮𝐫𝐢𝐬𝐦 𝐃𝐚𝐲, 𝐜𝐞𝐥𝐞𝐛𝐫𝐚𝐭𝐞 𝐭𝐡𝐞 𝐭𝐡𝐞𝐦𝐞: “𝐓𝐨𝐮𝐫𝐢𝐬𝐦 𝐚𝐧𝐝 𝐒𝐮𝐬𝐭𝐚𝐢𝐧𝐚𝐛𝐥𝐞 𝐓𝐫𝐚𝐧𝐬𝐟𝐨𝐫𝐦𝐚𝐭𝐢𝐨𝐧” by embracing responsible travel that benefits local communities, preserves culture, and protects the environment. Voluntourism is a rising trend, especially among Millennials and Gen Z, where travel becomes a meaningful mission to give back through education, conservation, and community projects.

This year, the call for “Tourism and Sustainable Transformation” encourages everyone to rethink how tourism is developed and experienced. It’s about balancing economic growth with preserving natural ecosystems and cultural heritage, while empowering local communities through inclusive policies and innovative practices. 

Together, these efforts transform tourism into a sustainable force that benefits both travelers and the places they visit. 🌍

Caption by: Patrick Blas
Pubmat by: Miguelito Lalu

#WTD2025

May be a graphic of 1 person, map and text that says "PATA SE History PAKTYERSHII ONTTT tamang bate World Tourism Day is commemorated annually on 27 September to foster awareness among the international community of the importance of tourism and its social, cultural, political, and economic value. September 27 27 Designed or Coincidence? The annual celebration of World Tourism Day was strategically picked to symbolize unity in tourism. World Tourism Day was established on September 27, 1970 because it marks the end of the tourism season in the Northern Hemisphere and the start of the tourism season in the Southern Hemisphere (Reali, 2025)."

May be an image of map and text that says "PATA 自に品 PATEISHIFONN tamang bote World Tourism Day 2025 Theme : Tourism Sustainable Transformation Tourism is not just about travel, it's the drive towards sustainable change. message.text:
Did you know tourism is making its strongest comeback in 2025?

𝐓𝐡𝐢𝐬 𝐖𝐨𝐫𝐥𝐝 𝐓𝐨𝐮𝐫𝐢𝐬𝐦 𝐃𝐚𝐲, 𝐜𝐞𝐥𝐞𝐛𝐫𝐚𝐭𝐞 𝐭𝐡𝐞 𝐭𝐡𝐞𝐦𝐞: “𝐓𝐨𝐮𝐫𝐢𝐬𝐦 𝐚𝐧𝐝 𝐒𝐮𝐬𝐭𝐚𝐢𝐧𝐚𝐛𝐥𝐞 𝐓𝐫𝐚𝐧𝐬𝐟𝐨𝐫𝐦𝐚𝐭𝐢𝐨𝐧” by embracing responsible travel that benefits local communities, preserves culture, and protects the environment. Voluntourism is a rising trend, especially among Millennials and Gen Z, where travel becomes a meaningful mission to give back through education, conservation, and community projects.

This year, the call for “Tourism and Sustainable Transformation” encourages everyone to rethink how tourism is developed and experienced. It’s about balancing economic growth with preserving natural ecosystems and cultural heritage, while empowering local communities through inclusive policies and innovative practices. 

Together, these efforts transform tourism into a sustainable force that benefits both travelers and the places they visit. 🌍

Caption by: Patrick Blas
Pubmat by: Miguelito Lalu

#PATAPHFEU
#WTD2025

media.accessibility_caption: May be an image of text that says "PATA သးထ PAITYERSHIFONTH PARTYERSH HIU ศ tamang bote WORLD Jourism JourismQay Qay "Tourism brings together" -Antonio Guterres"

May be a graphic of 1 person, map and text that says "PATA SE History PAKTYERSHII ONTTT tamang bate World Tourism Day is commemorated annually on 27 September to foster awareness among the international community of the importance of tourism and its social, cultural, political, and economic value. September 27 27 Designed or Coincidence? The annual celebration of World Tourism Day was strategically picked to symbolize unity in tourism. World Tourism Day was established on September 27, 1970 because it marks the end of the tourism season in the Northern Hemisphere and the start of the tourism season in the Southern Hemisphere (Reali, 2025)."

May be an image of map and text that says "PATA 自に品 PATEISHIFONN tamang bote World Tourism Day 2025 Theme : Tourism Sustainable Transformation Tourism is not just about travel, it's the drive towards sustainable change. With this year's theme, "Tourism and Sustainable Transformation", highlights how tourism celebrates its power as an agent of positive change. When done responsibly, tourişm benefits the locals, preserves cultural heritage, fosters economic growth, and promotes environmental conservation."

May be an image of tree and text that says "PATA သးသသး။ PARTYERSHIIOHTT PARTYERSHI tamang bote Volunteerism and Voluntourism Volunteerism comes in many forms but each action portrays single message the spirit of service, responsibility, and solidarity. The growing popularity of voluntourism reflects broader tourism trends (McGehee, 2014), especially among Millennials and Gen who value global citizenship and meaningful engagement (Bank,2021). Through voluntourism, they contribute education, conservation, and community projects turning travel into something more meaningful and sustainable. This makes every travel mission and a destination that benefits both the visitor and the host community."

message.text:
Did you know tourism is making its strongest comeback in 2025?

𝐓𝐡𝐢𝐬 𝐖𝐨𝐫𝐥𝐝 𝐓𝐨𝐮𝐫𝐢𝐬𝐦 𝐃𝐚𝐲, 𝐜𝐞𝐥𝐞𝐛𝐫𝐚𝐭𝐞 𝐭𝐡𝐞 𝐭𝐡𝐞𝐦𝐞: “𝐓𝐨𝐮𝐫𝐢𝐬𝐦 𝐚𝐧𝐝 𝐒𝐮𝐬𝐭𝐚𝐢𝐧𝐚𝐛𝐥𝐞 𝐓𝐫𝐚𝐧𝐬𝐟𝐨𝐫𝐦𝐚𝐭𝐢𝐨𝐧” by embracing responsible travel that benefits local communities, preserves culture, and protects the environment. Voluntourism is a rising trend, especially among Millennials and Gen Z, where travel becomes a meaningful mission to give back through education, conservation, and community projects.

This year, the call for “Tourism and Sustainable Transformation” encourages everyone to rethink how tourism is developed and experienced. It’s about balancing economic growth with preserving natural ecosystems and cultural heritage, while empowering local communities through inclusive policies and innovative practices. 

Together, these efforts transform tourism into a sustainable force that benefits both travelers and the places they visit. 🌍

Caption by: Patrick Blas
Pubmat by: Miguelito Lalu

#PATAPHFEU
#WTD2025
